            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en">The mighty king Ping (of Chu) approached Zheng Shou, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en">and asked him in the ancestral temple: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en">saying: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en">“Disaster and defeat have befallen and shaken the state of Chu, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en">I fear that the spirits (of my ancestors) will be angry because of this, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en">and cause the former kings to have no returning place, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en">how could I change (this)?” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en">Zheng Shou initially did not dare answering. </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en">The king insisted to seek his advice. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en">He answered: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en">“You should destroy the new capitals of Cheng Ling and Lin Yang, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en">kill the helping minister Yuan and the minor official Wu Ji.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en">The king said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en">“I cannot.” </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en">Zheng Shou said: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en">“If you cannot, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en">both the ruler and the state of Chu will have to fear calamities.” </seg>
                </p>

            <p>
                    <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en">Zheng Shou reported that he was sick, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en">and did not serve. </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en">The next year, the king saw Zheng Shou again, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en">Zheng Shou came out, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en">waiting while squatting on the road, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en">the king talked a bit with him, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en">the king derided him saying: </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en">“Last winter you said that the country will lose me, </seg>
               <seg corresp="#KR2p0063_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en">how about the present [situation]?” </seg>
                </p>

         </div>
